sor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":37,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Burguillon was born about 1418, in England. She had at least 1 daughter with Robert Burguillon."},"et":{"about 1418–":"umbes 1418–Surnud","1414–Male":"1414–Surnud","1440–1497":"1440–1497","1418–Female":"1418–Surnud","1414":"1414","about 1418":"umbes 1418","1455":"1455","1497":"1497","1440":"1440","1418":"1418","Burford, Somerset, England":"Burford, Somerset, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1418–":"noin 1418–Kuollut","1414–Male":"1414–Kuollut","1440–1497":"1440–1497","1418–Female":"1418–Kuollut","1414":"1414","about 1418":"noin 1418","1455":"1455","1497":"1497","1440":"1440","1418":"1418","Burford, Somerset, England":"Burford, Somerset, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1418–":"environ 1418–Décédée","1414–Male":"1414–Décédé","1440–1497":"1440–1497","1418–Female":"1418–Décédée","1414":"1414","about 1418":"envi